thread.title: Defense lifts Stony Point to first district football win
thread.title_full: Defense lifts Stony Point to first district football win | www.statesman.com

author: Sean Shapiro
title: Defense lifts Stony Point to first district football win
text:
Stony Point picked up its first District 13-6A victory of the season, blanking Westwood at Dragon Stadium 10-0 Oct. 16.
Stony Point (4-3, 1-3) limited Westwood to 137 yards, forced seven punts and recovered a fumble in the fourth quarter as Westwood was driving into Stony Point territory. The Tigers recorded their second shutout of the season while snapping a three-game losing streak.
Westwood’s defense allowed 352 total yards, but the Warriors also forced two turnovers and blocked a field-goal attempt in the fourth quarter.
Stony Point flexed its defensive muscle in a 10-0 win over Westwood Oct. 16.Jamie Harms/for Round Rock Leader Dom Williams scored Stony Point’s only touchdown on his first carry of the game, a 25-yard scamper down the left sideline that came late in the second quarter. Santiago Maya added a 28-yard field goal in the third quarter.
Michael Scroggins finished with 71 yards on 10 carries for the Tigers while Tanner Aenchbacher completed 10 of 13 passes for 155 yards.
Jack Swensen completed 13 of 23 passes for 91 yards for Westwood (0-7, 0-4).
